rings torsion springs in the case of the photo above are working properly and are not the issue.";i:31;s:39:"Garage Door Closes Part Way Then Opens.";i:32;s:91:"This has happened every time it gets cold for the last two years and Im getting sick of it.";i:33;s:85:"My garage door will start to close and when it gets to a certain point opens back up.";i:34;s:66:"Ive tried looking this up online and cant find a fix for my issue.";i:35;s:111:"When the door is in any position other than closed and the garage door opener is activated the door will close.";i:36;s:144:"If the garage door makes contact with an obstruction while closing the door will reverse the opener will beep and the lights will flash 5 times.";i:37;s:167:"If the door closes before that set distance has been completed then the opener thinks theres an error and automatically reverses to prevent property damages or injury.";i:38;s:174:"This setting could have been incorrectly set or changes in the weather could cause the door to expand and contract affecting the total distance the door travels as it cycles.";i:39;s:158:"Much of the door weight is held by the spring assembly if those springs are not adjusted correctly then there may be too much weight for the opener to handle.";i:40;s:202:"If door weight exceeds a certain amount the safety systems in the opener will stop opening and close the door again to prevent damage to the opener the door or anything that might be caught on the door.";i:41;s:145:"Garage door opens part way then reverses If your garage door opens part way then stops it could be that that its hitting or resting on something.";i:42;s:169:"There is a safety mechanism to prevent the door from crushing people so check to ensure that debris tools toys or anything else is not preventing the door from shutting.";i:43;s:74:"A garage door that only opens halfway becomes a nuisance for many reasons.";i:44;s:87:"Quite often the cause of your doors malfunction is an improperly set garage door limit.";i:45;s:54:"Open the garage door and watch it closely as it opens.";i:46;s:118:"When the garage door opens about halfway or 5 feet from the ground and stops the up limit switch needs to be adjusted.";i:47;s:34:"Test your door balance and weight.";i:48;s:196:"If the door moves freely and without much effort or the trolley still does not move with the door disconnected you might have some failure inside the opener itself that is causing binding or drag.";i:49;s:132:"Another possibility could be an intermittent connection somewhere that opens due to the movement or vibration as the opener engages.";i:50;s:141:"The symptom of this is a garage door that is in constant motion opening fully then immediately descending only to start the same cycle again.";i:51;s:74:"There may also be loose wire connections inside the button housing itself.";i:52;s:99:"As these wires short against the housing the electrical impulse causes the door opener to activate.";}}